sentence: Technology stocks were recording small gains, with shares of tech companies in the S&P 500 climbing about 0.2% in recent trade.
In company news, Park Electrochemical Corp ( PKE ) declined Thursday after the electronic components company reported falling fiscal Q2 net income and sales compared with year-ago levels.
Excluding one-time items, Park earned $0.10 per share, down from $0.23 per share during the same quarter last year.
Net sales dropped 23.2% year-over-year to $29.1 million.
Analyst estimates were not available for comparison.
PKE shares were down almost 8% at $16.32 each, earlier sinking to a session low of $15.70 a share.
